<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,279,413]" pageId="9" pageNumber="444">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[284,367,281,304]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Finotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[284,367,281,304]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="444">Finotia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the absence of wings and Krauss's organ, and the tympanum partially covered. The presence/absence of the Krauss's organ is a character used to divide 
<taxonomicName box="[1094,1245,316,341]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pamphagidae</taxonomicName>
into subfamilies (e.g., Storozhenko &amp; Paik 
<number box="[449,509,352,376]" pageId="9" pageNumber="444" value="2011.0">2011</number>
); the loss of this ancestral character in the genera 
<taxonomicName box="[1069,1152,353,376]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Finotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1152,353,376]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="444">Finotia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1206,1320,351,376]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Ocneridia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1206,1320,351,376]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="444">Ocneridia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered apomorphic, and consequently it does not seem useful to distinguish subfamilies (cf. Massa 
<number box="[1311,1372,388,412]" pageId="9" pageNumber="444" value="2012.0">2012</number>
a).
</paragraph>
